<Link id="l00858" /><CodeLine lineNumber="858"><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;&#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00859" /><CodeLine lineNumber="859"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; @&#125; // endgoup LLVMCTLTO</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00860" /><CodeLine lineNumber="860"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; @defgroup LLVMCTLTO&#95;CACHING ThinLTO Cache Control</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00861" /><CodeLine lineNumber="861"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; @ingroup LLVMCTLTO</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00862" /><CodeLine lineNumber="862"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00863" /><CodeLine lineNumber="863"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; These entry points control the ThinLTO cache. The cache is intended to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00864" /><CodeLine lineNumber="864"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; support incremental builds, and thus needs to be persistent across builds.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00865" /><CodeLine lineNumber="865"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; The client enables the cache by supplying a path to an existing directory.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00866" /><CodeLine lineNumber="866"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; The code generator will use this to store objects files that may be reused</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00867" /><CodeLine lineNumber="867"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; during a subsequent build.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00868" /><CodeLine lineNumber="868"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; To avoid filling the disk space, a few knobs are provided:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00869" /><CodeLine lineNumber="869"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;  - The pruning interval limits the frequency at which the garbage collector</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00870" /><CodeLine lineNumber="870"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;    will try to scan the cache directory to prune expired entries.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00871" /><CodeLine lineNumber="871"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;    Setting to a negative number disables the pruning.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00872" /><CodeLine lineNumber="872"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;  - The pruning expiration time indicates to the garbage collector how old an</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00873" /><CodeLine lineNumber="873"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;    entry needs to be to be removed.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00874" /><CodeLine lineNumber="874"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;  - Finally, the garbage collector can be instructed to prune the cache until</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00875" /><CodeLine lineNumber="875"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;    the occupied space goes below a threshold.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00876" /><CodeLine lineNumber="876"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; @&#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00877" /><CodeLine lineNumber="877"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00878" /><CodeLine lineNumber="878"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00879" /><CodeLine lineNumber="879"><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;&#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00880" /><CodeLine lineNumber="880"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; Sets the path to a directory to use as a cache storage for incremental build.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00881" /><CodeLine lineNumber="881"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; Setting this activates caching.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00882" /><CodeLine lineNumber="882"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00883" /><CodeLine lineNumber="883"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; \\since LTO&#95;API&#95;VERSION=18</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00884" /><CodeLine lineNumber="884"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00885" /><CodeLine lineNumber="885" lineLink="/docs/api/groups/llvmctlto-caching/#ga6ec37b4d07f9ca12a6dd7c425ea32f97"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">extern</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">void</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/groups/llvmctlto-caching/#ga6ec37b4d07f9ca12a6dd7c425ea32f97">thinlto&#95;codegen&#95;set&#95;cache&#95;dir</a>(<a href="/docs/api/groups/llvmclto/#gaad92d29c62685dde82e298596453c415">thinlto&#95;code&#95;gen&#95;t</a> cg,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00886" /><CodeLine lineNumber="886"><Highlight kind="normal">                                          </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">char</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &#42;cache&#95;dir);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00887" /><CodeLine lineNumber="887"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00888" /><CodeLine lineNumber="888"><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;&#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00889" /><CodeLine lineNumber="889"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; Sets the cache pruning interval (in seconds). A negative value disables the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00890" /><CodeLine lineNumber="890"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; pruning. An unspecified default value will be applied, and a value of 0 will</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00891" /><CodeLine lineNumber="891"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; force prunning to occur.</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00898" /><CodeLine lineNumber="898"><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;&#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00899" /><CodeLine lineNumber="899"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; Sets the maximum cache size that can be persistent across build, in terms of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00900" /><CodeLine lineNumber="900"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; percentage of the available space on the disk. Set to 100 to indicate</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00901" /><CodeLine lineNumber="901"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; no limit, 50 to indicate that the cache size will not be left over half the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00902" /><CodeLine lineNumber="902"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; available space. A value over 100 will be reduced to 100, a value of 0 will</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00903" /><CodeLine lineNumber="903"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; be ignored. An unspecified default value will be applied.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00904" /><CodeLine lineNumber="904"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00905" /><CodeLine lineNumber="905"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; The formula looks like:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00906" /><CodeLine lineNumber="906"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;  AvailableSpace = FreeSpace + ExistingCacheSize</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00907" /><CodeLine lineNumber="907"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;  NewCacheSize = AvailableSpace &#42; P/100</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00908" /><CodeLine lineNumber="908"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00909" /><CodeLine lineNumber="909"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; \\since LTO&#95;API&#95;VERSION=18</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00910" /><CodeLine lineNumber="910"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
